Even though it manages to stream video, it fails in every way. First off when I go to change some option for example video settings for a few seconds I can see a bunch options that quickly disappear before I can even tap on them. Some options that have been avaliable near the time when I initnially purchased this app like app privacy which let you select which apps could be streamed is now gone and I can't find it anywhere. For example: I can see an option that lets you change the stream format from mp4 to whatever, but I cannot tap on the setting to change it because it disappears. Attempting to interact with the disappearing settings opens a "Screen Stream Mirroring Pro stopped working" error message. The company does not reply to emails where I ask for help. Reinstalling the app did not help with any issues that I am having. Some options like framerate have only a slider with no number visible, while things like bitrate let you type the exact number. App can't decide in what language it is, some options are in the language that my OS is running in, some options are in English. "Force landscape display" does absolutely nothing. I purchased it because I am not able to stream via miracast and such due to my router being bad, but I feel like I'd rather just not be able to stream than have options that disappear. Also makes my phone (Redmi Note 8 Pro) get hot to the touch WHILE NOT STREAMING Furthermore, connecting it to OBS is a JOKE! tcp stream just flat out does not work. rtsp works sometimes with no real way to tell why it does or doesnt. Hi,

content: I'm using it on a rooted Nexus 7 and an unrooted Galaxy Nexus LTE and it works great on both.

I tried out a number of these screen recorders before finding this one.  Works great on a non-rooted Nexus 7, I didn't want to chance messing up my device by rooting it.   Snap to get the screen share working even with the extra step.  Thanks for making a great product.

This is the only screen mirroring/streaming product for Android that I found that did not require rooting the device.   The authors have developed a very novel approach: by running a script on your laptop while the android device is attached, via USB, a temporary change is made.   Support is excellent, responding in less that an hour to e-mails and then supporting me through the process -- the computer the android device will stream to must be in the same network as the android device. It was a very simple problem and the support stayed with me until it was figured out.  The only downside is a delay before changes on the android screen appear on the computer screen. I use this for software demos. Once you know this, there is no problem. This is a very well written, sophisticated product.
